<br>
10k may be pocket change to you, but I have never had that much at any one time.<br>
<br>
Also, I would never, under any circumstances, intentionally train anyone. That's a poor solution to the problem.<br>
<br>
My intent was not to flame anyone who has bought or sold an mq (I stated that in my previous post, but I'm not sure you caught it). My point is that people paying 10 to 12k for an mq (which is a lot of money to some of us) only encourages people to camp mobs that are already a bottlneck (Raster, KC and Chardok pipes) and adds to the frustation of those of us who are trying to get their epic without having to farm 20 or 30k. <br>
<br>
If you want to buy your epic and have the means to do so, then more power to you. Be aware, however, that you are only adding fuel to a fire that I (and I think a lot of others) would prefer to see die down, rather than continue to grow. <br>
